{"id":14881429,"mediaExerciseId":"6bd99042-3ae9-4c30-9e9e-f13073a22eeb","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"13","chapterTitle":"Return, Risk, and The Security Market Line","groupId":612378,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":456,"solutions":[{"id":6006166,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to assess the monthly stock prices for Colgate-Palmolive. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/3b23c78f905abcbdb4f82052bd22aabf/c7546e3c613bf13eb4057a2fb43bc177/lateximg_large.png","width":1105},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/3b23c78f905abcbdb4f82052bd22aabf/c7546e3c613bf13eb4057a2fb43bc177/lateximg.png","width":552}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"To begin, go to finance.yahoo.com and download Colgate-Palmolive's ending monthly stock prices for the preceding 60 months. This spreadsheet will provide all of the information needed to complete this activity.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/3b23c78f905abcbdb4f82052bd22aabf/2b3fac299848b45c185b85629f3ea03b/lateximg_large.png","width":1100},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/3b23c78f905abcbdb4f82052bd22aabf/2b3fac299848b45c185b85629f3ea03b/lateximg.png","width":549}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Then go to the St. Louis Federal Reserve website and get the three-month Treasury bill secondary market rate. This file will include historical risk-free rates in this dataset.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":98,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/3b23c78f905abcbdb4f82052bd22aabf/b4f2888cc068403fb3a2895e66776346/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/3b23c78f905abcbdb4f82052bd22aabf/b4f2888cc068403fb3a2895e66776346/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"After downloading the files, you can now calculate the average monthly returns of the securities. The average returns are calculated as follows:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{AR}&={\\dfrac{\\text{1}}{\\text{T}}}{\\sum_\\text{t = 1}^{\\text{T}}} {\\text{R}_\\text{ t}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere: \n\nT = Year\nR = Realized return \nAR = Average return\n\nEnter the supplied data into the formula above to calculate the average annual return of each asset. **Through the procedure above, you can determine the Colgate-Palmolive average monthly returns for the last 60 months.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":425,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/3b23c78f905abcbdb4f82052bd22aabf/e3028ef8a31016382f7ee3710fc9c67e/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":214,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/3b23c78f905abcbdb4f82052bd22aabf/e3028ef8a31016382f7ee3710fc9c67e/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Next, you need to determine the variance of each asset from the last 60 months. We can determine the standard deviation by finding the square root of the variance. \n\nThe variance of the stock's return is computed as follows: \n\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{V}&={\\dfrac{\\text{1}}{\\text{T - 1}}}{\\sum_\\text{t = 1}^{\\text{T}}} {\\text{(R - AR)}^\\text{ 2}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere: \n\nT = Year\nR = Realized return \nV = Variance\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":351,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/3b23c78f905abcbdb4f82052bd22aabf/85b33de975b4b9c1990bd3bdf929cc6d/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":177,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/3b23c78f905abcbdb4f82052bd22aabf/85b33de975b4b9c1990bd3bdf929cc6d/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"After determining the variance, you can now compute the standard deviation by using the formula below. \n\nThe standard deviation of returns is computed as follows: \n\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Standard deviation}&= {\\sqrt { V}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere: \nV = Variance\n\n**You may calculate the standard deviations for Colgate-Palmolive stock, the three-month Treasury bill, and the S&P 500 for the period using the formula from steps 5 and 6.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"560d6413-94c1-4b8e-acbb-48b14f9aef49","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881430,"exerciseName":"2","page":457,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"72f3c03b-6776-4e8b-a34f-1ecbec9f0601","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-minicase-questions-2-72f3c03b-6776-4e8b-a34f-1ecbec9f0601"},{"id":14881431,"exerciseName":"3","page":457,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"511aefe3-359e-4f68-82f5-d065d4ec3e82","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-minicase-questions-3-511aefe3-359e-4f68-82f5-d065d4ec3e82"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881427,"exerciseName":"28","page":455,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"c9379569-218f-45e3-991d-561029e4cd14","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-minicase-questions-28-c9379569-218f-45e3-991d-561029e4cd14"},{"id":14881426,"exerciseName":"27","page":455,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"38dfb401-5554-4008-8701-06a9f623a257","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-minicase-questions-27-38dfb401-5554-4008-8701-06a9f623a257"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-minicase-questions-1-6bd99042-3ae9-4c30-9e9e-f13073a22eeb"}